cs.CR, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SE, cs.PL

The paper discusses a protocol for executing smart contracts on a blockchain, which involves security and distributed computing aspects. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also involves distributed computing, which suggests cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) as the second likely category. The use of blockchain technology and the focus on correctness and verifiability suggest cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) as the third likely category. The paper also involves software engineering aspects, such as programming tools and optimization, which suggest cs.SE (Software Engineering) as the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper discusses smart contract execution, which suggests cs.PL (Programming Languages) as the fifth likely category.
